column4: Tesla's Musk woos Texas lawmakers  talks track  car plant
column5: AUSTIN  Texas/DETROIT Tesla Motors CEO Elon Musk urged Texas lawmakers on Thursday to ease restrictions on sales of his electric luxury cars as he floated the prospect of locating a new car factory or a test facility for his "hyperloop" mass transit concept in the state.

column4: CORRECTED-Tesla to hike electric car output to 'a few million' by 2025
column5: DETROIT  Jan 13 Tesla Motors Inc plans to boost production of electric cars to "at least a few million a year" by 2025 from fewer than 40 000 last year  Chief Executive Officer Elon Musk said Tuesday.

column4: Intel forecasts disappointing revenue; shares fall
column5: Chipmaker Intel Corp  forecast current-quarter revenue and gross margins that disappointed investors  sending its shares down more than 2 percent in extended trading.

column4: Virgin  Qualcomm to invest in Internet-via-satellite venture
column5: CAPE CANAVERAL  Fla. Richard Branson's Virgin Group and Qualcomm Inc will invest in a venture to build and fly a constellation of 648 satellites that can provide high-speed  global Internet access  company officials said on Thursday.
